HEADWORD: Isothermobathic
<hw>I`so*ther`mo*bath"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to an isothermobath; possessing or indicating equal
temperatures in a vertical section, as of the ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

